metadata.name: Lazarus
metadata.description:
A love letter to the mountains who keep me: 

Tucked away, in one of your many contours, I admire you. I live for you and everything you offer me, and in return I acknowledge the power you have to take everything that I am. 

I’ve guessed at your intention, and will continue to search for your meaning in this world, as I continue to search for my own. 

You Inspire me, impossibly, endlessly. You’ve taught me respect, awareness, love. Allow me to imagine, how we would be, if I were less afraid.

The mountains are my sanctuary.
